a
L=\sqrt{1^2+a^2}+\sqrt{2^2+(b - a)^2}+\sqrt{1^2+(4-b)^2}
a (3 a + 2 b) = b^2\ \rightarrow\ a = b/3
\frac{\partial L}{\partial b} = \frac{b-a}{\sqrt{(b-a)^2+4}}-\frac{4-b}{\sqrt{(4-b)^2+1}}
b = 3 \rightarrow a = 1
